1. Make 'tests' package (directory with __init__ file)
2. Make packages for each app, e.g. 'accounts', 'common', etc...
3. Make packages for each python file that makes sence to make tests for, e.g. 'views', 'custom_validators', 'utils', etc...
4. Check run configuration (python, env)
5. Import app and files into the packages init file, e.g.:
    - In 'tests/__init.py__':
        from .accounts import *
    - In 'tests/accounts/__init.py__':
        from .views import *
    - In 'tests/accounts/views/__init.py__':
        from .register_view_tests import *
6. Make a description what to test
7. Write tests
